dc/elements/1.1/"\n	xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"\n	xmlns:sy="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/"\n	xmlns:slash="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/"\n	>\n\n<channel>\n	<title>Timely &#187; Blog</title>\n	<atom:link href="http://time.ly/blog/feed/" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" />\n	<link>http://time.ly</link>\n	<description>The World’s Event Calendar</description>\n	<lastBuildDate>Tue, 21 Apr 2015 13:29:15 +0000</lastBuildDate>\n	<language>en-US</language>\n	<sy:updatePeriod>hourly</sy:updatePeriod>\n	<sy:updateFrequency>1</sy:updateFrequency>\n	\n	<item>\n		<title>2.2 Beta Now Available</title>\n		<link>http://time.ly/2-2-beta-now-available/</link>\n		<comments>http://time.ly/2-2-beta-now-available/#comments</comments>\n		<pubDate>Wed, 28 Jan 2015 22:26:43 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Jeffrey Wilcox]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://time.ly/?p=236046</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>Get the Beta now This is a beta release. It could very well break your site. Do not use it on your live site. The beta for our next release, 2.2, is now available. It contains some great new features and a massive pile of bug fixes. Let&#8217;s have a look at some of the...</p>\n<p><a class="excerpt-read-more btn btn-primary" href="http://time.ly/2-2-beta-now-available/" title="Read2.2 Beta Now Available">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly/2-2-beta-now-available/">2.2 Beta Now Available</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		<wfw:commentRss>http://time.ly/2-2-beta-now-available/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n		<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Free Hosted Calendars Temporarily Unavailable</title>\n		<link>http://time.ly/free-hosted-calendars-temporarily-unavailable/</link>\n		<comments>http://time.ly/free-hosted-calendars-temporarily-unavailable/#comments</comments>\n		<pubDate>Wed, 17 Dec 2014 02:01:04 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Jeffrey Wilcox]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://time.ly/?p=212996</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>For the next 24hrs we will not be able to provide free Hosted Calendars. Pro and Hub calendars are not affected, you are welcome to purchase those. Also, if you already have a calendar you will not experience any issues. We hope to have this resolved ASAP, watch here for updates.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly/free-hosted-calendars-temporarily-unavailable/">Free Hosted Calendars Temporarily Unavailable</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		<wfw:commentRss>http://time.ly/free-hosted-calendars-temporarily-unavailable/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n		<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Malware Reported on aggregator.time.ly</title>\n		<link>http://time.ly/malware-reported-aggregator-time-ly/</link>\n		<comments>http://time.ly/malware-reported-aggregator-time-ly/#comments</comments>\n		<pubDate>Mon, 15 Dec 2014 18:12:50 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Jeffrey Wilcox]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://time.ly/?p=211868</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>If you are experiencing issues with the buy tickets button resulting in a 404 or a malware warning from Google, please update to the latest version of the calendar. Some months ago we began tracking clicks on the “Buy tickets” button as we were interested in building a ticketing add-on. The data we collected was...</p>\n<p><a class="excerpt-read-more btn btn-primary" href="http://time.ly/malware-reported-aggregator-time-ly/" title="ReadMalware Reported on aggregator.time.ly">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly/malware-reported-aggregator-time-ly/">Malware Reported on aggregator.time.ly</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		<wfw:commentRss>http://time.ly/malware-reported-aggregator-time-ly/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n		<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>2.1.9 Updated Beta</title>\n		<link>http://time.ly/2-1-9-updated-beta/</link>\n		<comments>http://time.ly/2-1-9-updated-beta/#comments</comments>\n		<pubDate>Wed, 03 Dec 2014 21:04:25 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Jeffrey Wilcox]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://time.ly/?p=204342</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>We have made some changes to the earlier beta, and a new release is available now. Thanks for sending in your bug reports! Here are the full release notes for this release. Features/Improvements Improved calendar feeds import from Google calendar Made calendar behaviour across browsers more consistent &#8211; fixed issue where some of the elements...</p>\n<p><a class="excerpt-read-more btn btn-primary" href="http://time.ly/2-1-9-updated-beta/" title="Read2.1.9 Updated Beta">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly/2-1-9-updated-beta/">2.1.9 Updated Beta</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		<wfw:commentRss>http://time.ly/2-1-9-updated-beta/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n		<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>2.1.9 Beta Available</title>\n		<link>http://time.ly/2-1-9-beta-available/</link>\n		<comments>http://time.ly/2-1-9-beta-available/#comments</comments>\n		<pubDate>Wed, 03 Dec 2014 12:07:06 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Jeffrey Wilcox]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[Releases]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://time.ly/?p=202570</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>We have been hard at work over the last two weeks and we now have 2.1.9 just about ready to go. You can download it now and let us know what you think. It contains numerous bug fixes. Removed unwanted URLs from print view Fixed multi day events display in Month view Improved legacy theme...</p>\n<p><a class="excerpt-read-more btn btn-primary" href="http://time.ly/2-1-9-beta-available/" title="Read2.1.9 Beta Available">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly/2-1-9-beta-available/">2.1.9 Beta Available</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		<wfw:commentRss>http://time.ly/2-1-9-beta-available/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n		<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Add beautiful (and legal) images to your events</title>\n		<link>http://time.ly/add-beautiful-legal-images-events/</link>\n		<comments>http://time.ly/add-beautiful-legal-images-events/#comments</comments>\n		<pubDate>Thu, 27 Nov 2014 20:33:21 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Rik Logtenberg]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Tips and Tricks]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://time.ly/?p=200099</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>Photos and images are the most engaging type of content on the Internet. Photos are a whopping 10x more likely to be shared. The more photos you have on your calendar, the more you will engage your audience. The best way to add images to your events is to get the original event poster as...</p>\n<p><a class="excerpt-read-more btn btn-primary" href="http://time.ly/add-beautiful-legal-images-events/" title="ReadAdd beautiful (and legal) images to your events">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly/add-beautiful-legal-images-events/">Add beautiful (and legal) images to your events</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		<wfw:commentRss>http://time.ly/add-beautiful-legal-images-events/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n		<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>2.1.7 Is Now Available</title>\n		<link>http://time.ly/2-1-7-now-available/</link>\n		<comments>http://time.ly/2-1-7-now-available/#comments</comments>\n		<pubDate>Fri, 21 Nov 2014 00:52:51 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Jeffrey Wilcox]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Calendar Insights]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[Releases]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://time.ly/?p=190825</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>2.1.7 was released today. It contains numerous bug fixes and some great new features and improvements. The most exciting is a new setting that forces Posterboard tiles to align in a grid. The setting is found in the Events &#62; Settings &#62; Add-ons &#62; Extended Views menu. Timely is all about making sure you can...</p>\n<p><a class="excerpt-read-more btn btn-primary" href="http://time.ly/2-1-7-now-available/" title="Read2.1.7 Is Now Available">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly/2-1-7-now-available/">2.1.7 Is Now Available</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		<wfw:commentRss>http://time.ly/2-1-7-now-available/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n		<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Black Monday Sale</title>\n		<link>http://time.ly/black-monday-sale/</link>\n		<comments>http://time.ly/black-monday-sale/#comments</comments>\n		<pubDate>Tue, 18 Nov 2014 23:36:09 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Jeffrey Wilcox]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://time.ly/?p=188646</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>The leaves are turning, the sun is setting early and the rain has set in here in our Vancouver HQ. With our WordPress products now all on sale, what better time to sit down with your site and upgrade your calendar? For a limited time we are offering all of our add-ons for half price!...</p>\n<p><a class="excerpt-read-more btn btn-primary" href="http://time.ly/black-monday-sale/" title="ReadBlack Monday Sale">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly/black-monday-sale/">Black Monday Sale</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		<wfw:commentRss>http://time.ly/black-monday-sale/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n		<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Facebook Add-on Temporarily Unavailable</title>\n		<link>http://time.ly/facebook-add-temporarily-unavailable/</link>\n		<comments>http://time.ly/facebook-add-temporarily-unavailable/#comments</comments>\n		<pubDate>Wed, 20 Aug 2014 19:40:30 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Jeffrey Wilcox]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://time.ly/?p=145256</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>In a series a updates made over the past several months Facebook has gradually closed and limited access points Timely users relied on to easily share their events. Gone is the ability to export events from Timely to Facebook and Importing events from pages you have liked or your friends has become increasingly difficult. Now...</p>\n<p><a class="excerpt-read-more btn btn-primary" href="http://time.ly/facebook-add-temporarily-unavailable/" title="ReadFacebook Add-on Temporarily Unavailable">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly/facebook-add-temporarily-unavailable/">Facebook Add-on Temporarily Unavailable</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		<wfw:commentRss>http://time.ly/facebook-add-temporarily-unavailable/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n		<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>2.1 Release</title>\n		<link>http://time.ly/2-1-release/</link>\n		<comments>http://time.ly/2-1-release/#comments</comments>\n		<pubDate>Wed, 30 Jul 2014 23:32:21 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Jeffrey Wilcox]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[Releases]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://time.ly/?p=130298</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>It&#8217;s coming! 2.1 was planned for this week, but we decided to take one more week for a bit more testing. We implemented some changes to CSS caching relatively late, and we want to make sure it&#8217;s working very smoothly. We decided it would be worth delaying to get these changes into this release. They make...</p>\n<p><a class="excerpt-read-more btn btn-primary" href="http://time.ly/2-1-release/" title="Read2.1 Release">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly/2-1-release/">2.1 Release</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		<wfw:commentRss>http://time.ly/2-1-release/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n		<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Architecting for Performance Part 2.</title>\n		<link>http://time.ly/architecting-performance-part-2/</link>\n		<comments>http://time.ly/architecting-performance-part-2/#comments</comments>\n		<pubDate>Thu, 24 Jul 2014 21:11:21 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Jeffrey Wilcox]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Technology]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://time.ly/?p=127148</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>Justas, our lead developer, has posted part 2 in his series on how to build performant plugins for WordPress. In the first instalment he focused on tools you can use to set a baseline, and measure the improvements you have made. In part 2 Justas talks about finding architectural patterns behind your code. Using some...</p>\n<p><a class="excerpt-read-more btn btn-primary" href="http://time.ly/architecting-performance-part-2/" title="ReadArchitecting for Performance Part 2.">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly/architecting-performance-part-2/">Architecting for Performance Part 2.</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		<wfw:commentRss>http://time.ly/architecting-performance-part-2/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n		<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Welcome to the Team Pavel!</title>\n		<link>http://time.ly/welcome-team-pavel/</link>\n		<comments>http://time.ly/welcome-team-pavel/#comments</comments>\n		<pubDate>Tue, 22 Jul 2014 22:24:33 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Jeffrey Wilcox]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://time.ly/?p=92034</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>Pavel is a Moscow native who spends half his year escaping the Russian winter in Goa. Pavel is an experienced developer who has worked for one of the largest news groups in Russia, and worked with a team that developed apps and digital signage for the Sochi Olympics. Pavel is also a music producer and...</p>\n<p><a class="excerpt-read-more btn btn-primary" href="http://time.ly/welcome-team-pavel/" title="ReadWelcome to the Team Pavel!">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly/welcome-team-pavel/">Welcome to the Team Pavel!</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		<wfw:commentRss>http://time.ly/welcome-team-pavel/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n		<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Changing Twig Template Variables</title>\n		<link>http://time.ly/changing-twig-template-variables/</link>\n		<comments>http://time.ly/changing-twig-template-variables/#comments</comments>\n		<pubDate>Tue, 22 Jul 2014 21:40:12 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Jeffrey Wilcox]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Calendar Insights]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[Technology]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://time.ly/?p=125799</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>We have received several requests from users to list Twig template variables. We have been reluctant to do so as we will be making breaking changes to these variables though our next several releases. Some variables we left for compatibility with pre 2.0 versions of the software, but these are deprecated and will be removed...</p>\n<p><a class="excerpt-read-more btn btn-primary" href="http://time.ly/changing-twig-template-variables/" title="ReadChanging Twig Template Variables">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly/changing-twig-template-variables/">Changing Twig Template Variables</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		<wfw:commentRss>http://time.ly/changing-twig-template-variables/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n		<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>How we Improved our Plugin&#8217;s Performance by over 20x</title>\n		<link>http://time.ly/improved-plugins-performance-20x/</link>\n		<comments>http://time.ly/improved-plugins-performance-20x/#comments</comments>\n		<pubDate>Fri, 27 Jun 2014 04:42:17 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Jeffrey Wilcox]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Technology]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://time.ly/?p=112485</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>When we started talking about our priorities for 2.0 performance was at the top of the list. WordPress has never been known for it&#8217;s blazing speed, and the calendar was on the slow side of a slow CMS. Visiting sites and watching that little loading icon spin was becoming excruciating. Last spring Justas, our lead...</p>\n<p><a class="excerpt-read-more btn btn-primary" href="http://time.ly/improved-plugins-performance-20x/" title="ReadHow we Improved our Plugin&#8217;s Performance by over 20x">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly/improved-plugins-performance-20x/">How we Improved our Plugin&#8217;s Performance by over 20x</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		<wfw:commentRss>http://time.ly/improved-plugins-performance-20x/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n		<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Introducing Our Newest Team Members</title>\n		<link>http://time.ly/introducing-newest-team-members/</link>\n		<comments>http://time.ly/introducing-newest-team-members/#comments</comments>\n		<pubDate>Wed, 28 May 2014 22:50:34 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Jeffrey Wilcox]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://time.ly/?p=92118</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>This spring we hired Ben and Lukas. Most of you have met Ben in the support forums, and some of our Pro users might have met Lukas as well. Ben is a developer from Croatia and previously worked for The Seed Studio. As some of you may remember, The Seed was the original creator of...</p>\n<p><a class="excerpt-read-more btn btn-primary" href="http://time.ly/introducing-newest-team-members/" title="ReadIntroducing Our Newest Team Members">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly/introducing-newest-team-members/">Introducing Our Newest Team Members</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://time.ly">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		<wfw:commentRss>http://time.ly/introducing-newest-team-members/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n		<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Changes to Facebook&#8217;s API</title>\n		<link>http://time.ly/changes-facebooks-api/</link>\n		<comments>http://time.ly/changes-facebooks-api/#comments</comments>\n		<pubDate>Wed, 28 May 2014 22:14:59 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Jeffrey Wilcox]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>\n\n		<guid